## Phase 3 — Lightbox Polish

**Goal**: The lightbox becomes a first-class image viewer. Fullscreen mode, keyboard shortcut
discoverability, GPS link, and an optional slideshow.

### 3a — Fullscreen mode

**File**: `src/ui/web/src/components/Lightbox.tsx`

Add a fullscreen toggle button in the lightbox header (top-right, alongside the existing Close
button). In fullscreen mode: the metadata panel is hidden, the image fills the entire screen.

**Implementation:**

```typescript
const [isFullscreen, setIsFullscreen] = useState(false);

// Sync with browser Fullscreen API
useEffect(() => {
  const onFsChange = () => setIsFullscreen(Boolean(document.fullscreenElement));
  document.addEventListener("fullscreenchange", onFsChange);
  return () => document.removeEventListener("fullscreenchange", onFsChange);
}, []);

const toggleFullscreen = () => {
  if (!isFullscreen) {
    lightboxRef.current?.requestFullscreen().catch(() => {
      // Fallback: use CSS-only fullscreen (position:fixed + z-[9999])
      setIsFullscreen(true);
    });
  } else {
    document.exitFullscreen?.();
  }
};
```

Keyboard: `F` key triggers `toggleFullscreen`. Add to existing `onKeyDown` handler:

```typescript
case "f":
case "F":
  toggleFullscreen();
  break;
```

Button appearance:

```tsx
<button
  onClick={toggleFullscreen}
  className="p-2 rounded-lg text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-800/60"
  aria-label={isFullscreen ? "Exit fullscreen" : "Enter fullscreen"}
>
  {isFullscreen
    ? <ArrowsPointingInIcon className="h-5 w-5" />
    : <ArrowsPointingOutIcon className="h-5 w-5" />
  }
</button>
```

In fullscreen, hide the metadata panel entirely:

