### 3d — Slideshow mode

**File**: `src/ui/web/src/components/Lightbox.tsx`

Space bar starts / stops an auto-advance slideshow (3-second interval by default). A thin
progress bar at the top of the lightbox animates from left to right over 3 seconds, then
resets when the image advances.

```typescript
const [slideshowActive, setSlideshowActive] = useState(false);
const slideshowRef = useRef<number>();

useEffect(() => {
  if (!slideshowActive) { clearInterval(slideshowRef.current); return; }
  slideshowRef.current = window.setInterval(() => {
    onNavigate(Math.min(currentIndex + 1, assets.length - 1));
  }, 3000);
  return () => clearInterval(slideshowRef.current);
}, [slideshowActive, currentIndex, assets.length, onNavigate]);
```

Add to `onKeyDown`:
```typescript
case " ":
  e.preventDefault(); // prevent page scroll
  setSlideshowActive(a => !a);
  break;
```

Progress bar (shown only while slideshow is running):

```tsx
{slideshowActive && (
  <div className="absolute top-0 inset-x-0 h-0.5 bg-gray-800 z-10">
    <div
      key={currentIndex} // remounts = restarts animation on each advance
      className="h-full bg-indigo-500 animate-[progress_3s_linear_forwards]
                 motion-reduce:animate-none"
    />
  </div>
)}
```

Add to `tailwind.config.js` theme extensions:

```js
keyframes: {
  progress: {
    from: { width: "0%" },
    to:   { width: "100%" },
  },
},
animation: {
  // "progress" animation already referenced above
},
```

Slideshow pauses automatically when the user manually navigates (prev/next arrow or arrow key).
Update the `onNavigate` handler to call `setSlideshowActive(false)` when triggered manually.

